[thinking] **Considering object serialization**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the serialization process. It has a `private final byte[] encoded` field. When the replacement object gets serialized, perhaps this field gets passed back into `replaceObject`, which might lead to recursive replacements. I wonder if the `ObjectOutputStream` is calling `replaceObject` for every object after that replacement as well? It feels like there are layers to unravel here regarding how replacements are handled in serialization.
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
