[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering object serialization**\n\nI'm thinking about the serialization process. It has a `private final byte[] encoded` field. When the replacement object gets serialized, perhaps this field gets passed back into `replaceObject`, which might lead to recursive replacements. I wonder if the `ObjectOutputStream` is calling `replaceObject` for every object after that replacement as well? It feels like there are layers to unravel here regarding how replacements are handled in serialization.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09b2dabd705074aa016a266327dfcc81978cfb33e87a0f7ded\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJmNLSMlcWkCefrto6dEMCemZVugObN6rc_6wN39KR_HkOy7-VvyZqFGIIYqNYOuiNskUQ-AVk57Lt_TvM5NX7yS0OL1RHY3TAPh4k1pkdWTEEh_RuyKlN1TvVCycYGqyLa0Pu2dkd_BdCQO3Cx1zvx67fEYLHCuu4otYmLku4CjhlCiqehkup2NTSDBslaAmMRjriIvstAJvt_RvGXl8QodVX116rZjBtJvGdF89Y3GwsugJ596opx2BD1DxF-6ft37GOzcCqTaRYW5PY82MnNWDLbYHK7tx3hix477hZBwfNi0zSWJaAwZaxOSbjIVBV4v7YYOebmhuDAZzuQH5ROck8SU5w5IQY_lPoYeAoe0m6Zm5yQ2W6Lw0k7qK3O7wgEoPJyq2pGxaVnWiZhVIRKv7LrnTC9IBSyOYGvzA7HeRM6zPdfn7_xABXo1_x6EbiNOIC2zuzXEyWYS5oCiqjdJP49evqU4MbSIfMogRWjDaRJxk51qlL2Ws37nru15ntJGlfkeJoH6BxwI2HZIrYVSbIEHzKmt-p9UlNwmbyhYGqHP5Snj-QsMGb2qWMiYsdJHGv0mO15QQQbXiDBfA3KMUl0YPLeLNXU-NPnDvjJC1xlU1SUj2diF7Ry-qDLWzpPf9eRyWtpBT5Zz21JZ4XipN1N7mn4UGwfv282EmWjS6DDh7PScLbR9LbDASC1h1QyiWXoNkSDEDBgjKYsblDJUOvQ0Bp2nmzEgg1R8MsOY-qMquyqJr4x9gq-xnNDxT_Wl9i_VsUJXIPWGpDa_gl5F3V3A77ec-m5-JH0ZvxQRghpeeGskihpDm28ycJ8L6eKypyRJ5l70dJgweuf9QoJ2AX62VQ7fmMmtsSfkc2zeQUpy5bvkdvyaJBRMdSkyva4YUJXkaIKZGAgRuTnF0GCH1xtgDyQjRHE-dnLZnUio2pQnX8_SW9WI_c7182S7Ls1vBO2BuEe_2yPuUidsOgTszk-jlchNO3wNMbQHtV5NpOPUvdFEqC-qYlFQjZy5bFiNqD7TAEUBKNNKMAxuSunv2KllLMhcR253aiPW_NrHMxcpe3w4tiJlx-k32qq9jO9jxBjzWgH75MfdbBkHRacwtMe51zXnxzU3YfkTe1Pps7fkjqvXLveAFpG8rdXQaHW_19l56fi0FfFeB-6v684gth7UeVZZI3xCzaUODWptse--aSk_A400_uCIPNeNDa84jODEdby3Ttp0Rq_KI